subjective.chief_complaint: Headache left side for few hours
subjective.hpi: Patient experienced gradual throbbing headache starting on left side few hours prior to visit. Visual symptoms included zigzag lines and blurred vision before onset of headache. Headache associated with photophobia, nausea with 2 episodes of vomiting today. No radiation of pain. No neck stiffness. Episodes of headache preceded by visual aura. Similar episode 2 weeks ago resolved with analgesia. No speech disturbance, no limb weakness/numbness, no fever, no rashes, no recent head injury. Patient expresses worry about brain cancer.
